Text:
You just indexed a file that's already seeding and has been reindexed by all major indexes since.  Had you googled "strahler physical geography torrent" you would have seen this, right? Or, more closely, had you searched TPB's index, you would have found this:  http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/7351751/ . Is there any use to your indexing a duplicate?

The sure way to kill a low volume torrent like this one is to duplicate it. In the long run, both the duplicated and the duplicate turn dead, for splitting a small number of seeders who become confused over which one is the good one.
